item.description:
274. H-Index #  Problem #  Given an array of citations (each citation is a non-negative integer) of a researcher, write a function to compute the researcher&rsquo;s h-index.
According to the definition of h-index on Wikipedia: &ldquo;A scientist has index h if h of his/her N papers have at least h citations each, and the other N − h papers have no more than h citations each.&rdquo;
Example 1:
